                        "category": "Packages",
                        "classification": "-",
                        "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:btrfs: fix inode list leak during backref walking atresolve_indirect_refs()During backref walking, at resolve_indirect_refs(), if we get an errorwe jump to the 'out' label and call ulist_free() on the 'parents' ulist,which frees all the elements in the ulist - however that does not freeany inode lists that may be attached to elements, through the 'aux' fieldof a ulist node, so we end up leaking lists if we have any attached tothe unodes.Fix this by calling free_leaf_list() instead of ulist_free() when we exitfrom resolve_indirect_refs(). The static function free_leaf_list() ismoved up for this to be possible and it's slightly simplified by removingunnecessary code.",
